 <text>
  <front>
   <head>INSCRIPTION FOR A ROOT-HOUSE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">FOND man! retire to this still cell,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And bid the busy world farewel;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Here seek the cherub Happiness,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who loves the quiet lone recess,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And shuns the city's noisy scene,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For pleasures tranquil and serene.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">How solemn is the oak's broad shade,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The naked grove seen thro' the glade,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The rock that high projects its steep,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The distant prospect of the deep!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Fond man! here cheerful may'st thou spend</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy swift-wing'd life, nor fear thy end;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Stealing thro' life, as thro' the plain</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yon rill in murmurs seeks the main.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Here, when the saffron-vested dawn</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Spreads radiance o'er the dewy lawn,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For hours exempt from woe and sin,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy ardent orison begin;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Here too at eve His praise display,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who led thee thro' the finish'd day.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
